    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Create and enable fingerprint ID on your device.\r\n2. Go to Settings -> Privacy & Security -> Switching Apps.\r\n3. Switch the \"Use fingerprint to unlock app\" toggle ON.\r\n4. Exit Settings menu and open a webpage.\r\n5. Tap on the 3-dot menu to invoke menu contents.\r\n6.  Minimize and restore the app.\r\n7. Touch fingerprint sensor.\r\n8. Observe if the 3-dot menu remains displayed.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nAfter dismissing the fingerprint verification window with the fingerprint, the 3-dot menu stays open on restore.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nAfter restoring the app, the webpage and the 3-dot menu can be seen for a slip second before the fingerprint verification window is invoked. Upon dismissing the window, the 3-dot menu is no longer displayed. \r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n* Android device: Xiaomi Redmi Note 8T (Android 9).\r\n* Focus version: 96.0.0-beta.1 (Build 353412232 GV 96.0-20211206194555), RC 95.1.0, latest debug build from main 12/09.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89388888/145383997-d66aa272-5c7d-439e-b6a2-8389d8693530.mp4\r\n",
